Execution Flow & History

(Open History / Execution Graph)

“Once the workflow is executed, WebGenie captures the execution flow and presents it visually through the History view.

Users can:

* review how the agent performed the workflow,
* replay or test the workflow again,
* refine or modify execution steps,
* and once satisfied, publish the workflow to the marketplace for reuse.”

⸻

Marketplace Vision

“This allows successful workflows to evolve into reusable enterprise capabilities that can be shared and reused across teams and business functions.”

⸻

Architecture & Business Value

“The architecture is designed around:

* portable browser extensions,
* AI orchestration services,
* connected enterprise integrations,
* execution tracing,
* and governance/audit capabilities.

The platform is designed for deployment through enterprise-supported browser extensions such as Chrome and Edge.

From a business perspective, WebGenie aims to:

* reduce repetitive manual effort,
* improve workflow efficiency,
* reduce context switching,
* improve operational consistency,
* and simplify cross-system workflow execution.

For supported workflows, we estimate:

* 60–75% reduction in task completion time,
* and approximately 2x–3x productivity improvement.”

